==English==

===Etymology===
{{wikipedia|Yahweh (name)}}
The usual scholarly reconstruction of the vocalization of the ''nomen tetragrammaton'',  Biblical {{etyl|he|en}} {{term|יהוה|sc=Hebr|lang=he}}. As ''[[Jahweh]]'' from the mid 19th century, ''Yahweh'' from the late 19th century. This reconstruction replaced the earlier ''[[Jehovah]]'' (in use since the Reformation, still in Shakespeare, (1597)   ''The deputy elected by the Lord'' (''Richard II'', 3.2.53).

===Proper noun===
'''Yahweh'''

# {{context|religion}} The personal name of God in the Hebrew Bible; 

